<HEADLINE>
FT  29 FEB 92 / Print leaders recommend deal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LEADERS of the GPMU print union yesterday recommended a deal which they say
would raise pay in line with inflation.
The proposed agreement with the British Printing Industries Federation would
increase craft rates by Pounds 4.45 a week on April 24 and Pounds 2.50 from
from August 24.
The federation, which represents 3,000 employers with a total of 50,000
workers, had originally pressed for a delay. The union opposed that and
proposals for more flexible working.
