FT  29 FEB 92 / Halifax offers Peps to companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HALIFAX, the largest building society, is offering businesses a
single-company Pep (personal equity plan) for employees.
The scheme, which is not available through branches or to individual
consumers, will enable employees of companies to set up single-company Peps
using shares acquired under employee share-option schemes.
Employees will be able to transfer Pounds 3,000 worth of shares directly
from share option schemes into the Pep in which capital gains will be exempt
from tax liability.
