<HEADLINE>
FT  29 FEB 92 / Briefcase, Q&amp;A: Limits on gifts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
IS IT possible for a parent to gift each child Pounds 3,000 pa without
future inheritance tax liability, or is a parent restricted to gifting a
total of Pounds 3,000 pa.
The Pounds 3,000 annual exemption is restricted to Pounds 3,000 for each
donor (plus any unused element of the previous year's exemption - but not
more than one year is available). If you make gifts to several people the
total of all gifts should not exceed Pounds 3,000: see section 19 of the
Inheritance Tax Act 1984.
No legal responsibility can be accepted by the Financial Times for the
answers given in these columns. All inquiries will be answered by post as
soon as possible.
