<HEADLINE>
FT  29 FEB 92 / Finance &amp; The Family (At A Glance): Eagle Star cuts bonuses
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Eagle Star Life has announced reduced reversionary and terminal bonuses on
its endowment and pension policies. Using the standard industry assumptions
that a policy was started by a 29-year-old man investing Pounds 30 per
month, 10-year pay-outs dropped from Pounds 7,449 to Pounds 6,896, while
25-year maturity values fell from Pounds 62,785 to Pounds 61,910. This is in
line with the industrial trend for 10-year policies to see a much sharper
cut than 25-year contracts.
