<HEADLINE>
FT  29 FEB 92 / The Lex Column: Cartels
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The European Court's ruling that Commission decisions should be signed in
all Community languages by Mr Jacques Delors brings to mind an ancient, but
alas defunct English legal defence that you cannot be successfully charged
by a policeman wearing his helmet back to front. Investors would be unwise
to assume, though, that other EC cartel culprits will now get their fines
quashed. The court tends to back Brussels where it can, so will doubtless be
capable of finding another technicality to uphold the Commission's appeal.
</TEXT>
