<HEADLINE>
FT  29 FEB 92 / Appointments: Bodies politic
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Professor Anthony Jones is to become the new rector and vice-provost of the
ROYAL COLLEGE OF ART from August 1. Jones, 47, was born in Wales and studied
sculpture and painting at Newport College of Art and Tulane University, New
Orleans. He was director of Glasgow School of Art for six years before
becoming president of the School of the Art Institute of Chicago in 1986.
*****
Brian Cook, md of Bankers Trust Co, has been elected chairman of the
American Banking and Securities Association of London.
*****
Robert Lacey has been appointed executive director for the Scottish branch
of the BRITISH RED CROSS.
*****
Richard Genochio, most recently general manager, public and government
affairs, at Texaco in London, has been appointed the first chief executive
of the DIRECT MARKETING ASSOCIATION.
*****
Carmen Callil is appointed a governor of the MUSEUM OF LONDON.
*****
John Southworth is appointed secretary and finance director of the Building
Employers Confederation.
*****
Roger Vaughan, joint chief executive of Swan Hunter, is appointed the 15th
and final member of the NATIONAL CURRICULUM COUNCIL. Five of his seven
children are still at state schools in Northumberland.
*****
Roger Trotman, md of Tufnol, has been elected president of EEF West
Midlands.
*****
Graham Mackenzie, chief executive of United Engineering Steels, has been
elected president of the Engineering Employers' Federation.
