   By MICHIYO NAKAMOTO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AMSTRAD, the consumer electronics group, is taking a 29.5 per cent stake in
Betacom, which designs and distributes telephones, as an investment.
Amstrad will acquire 26.5 per cent from Cannon Street Investments and 3 per
cent from Mr Alan Sugar, its chairman. The price is 18p per share; Mr Sugar
