FT  29 FEB 92 / UK Company News: BICC buys east German cables maker for
Pounds 22m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JANE FULLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BICC, the cables and construction group, is buying one of the leading cable
businesses in what used to be East Germany for DM63m (Pounds 22m).
KWO, which has four factories in the Berlin area, is being bought from the
Treuhand, the government agency responsible for privatising former
state-owned concerns. It makes power cables and metallic and optical
telephone cables.
Last year KWO had turnover of DM310m and it lost DM32m pre-tax. That
excluded 'excess employee costs' of DM70m, which BICC said it was not
assuming. BICC has agreed to a DM80m investment programme over the next two
years.
