FT  28 FEB 92 / Commodities and Agriculture: Falconbridge to restart number
one smelter
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FALCONBRIDGE of Canada is to restart the number one smelter at Falconbridge
Dominicana, its ferro-nickel facility in the Dominican Republic, in
mid-March, writes Bernard Simon in Toronto. The smelter was closed last
October because of the weak state of the nickel market. Falcondo has an
annual capacity of 32,000 tonnes of ferro-nickel. The closure of the smelter
cut production by half.
