<HEADLINE>
FT  28 FEB 92 / UK News (Employment): Tribunal tells port to pay cost of
case
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AN INDUSTRIAL tribunal yesterday took the unusual step of awarding costs
against an employer which had lost an unfair dismissal case, Catherine
Milton writes.
The tribunal ruled in August that the Port of London Authority had unfairly
dismissed 19 dockworkers at Tilbury because they were union activists. The
case lasted 196 days.
Legal experts said that the tribunal must believe the authority had
conducted the case unreasonably, and costs were likely to run into six
figures when they were assessed. The tribunal is expected to issue reasons
today.
The authority is appealing against both the unfair dismissal ruling and a
tribunal order that 12 of the 19 dockworkers should get their jobs back. The
appeal is likely to last another week.
