FT  28 FEB 92 / Modest inflow of funds to unit trusts
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UNIT TRUSTS had only a modest inflow of funds last month in spite of the
launch of 12 trusts.
Net investment (gross sales minus repurchases) was Pounds 26.8m, which was
the worst figure since September 1990. The number of unitholder accounts
fell slightly again to 4.44m
Gross sales for the month were Pounds 668.5m and repurchases were Pounds
641.7m. The value of the funds under management was boosted by buoyant stock
markets to Pounds 57.5bn.
