</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Gulf War caused irreparable damage to the environment and its legacy
poses a serious health hazard, according to a Greenpeace survey released
today. .
The war 'has resulted in an unprecedented disaster for the region, which has
been left with a serious impact on the sea, land and atmosphere that will
take years to heal,' the group concluded. The Meteorological Office in
London has said its studies of the region indicate the damage is not as bad
as first predicted, although long-term effects could take years to emerge.
