<TEXT>
GREENCORE, the Irish sugar and foods group, held a stormy annual meeting in
Dublin yesterday, the first since its privatisation last April.
A heated debate took place over the re-election of three directors who had
sat on the board of the company before privatisation and during 1988 and
1990,a period in which a series of controversial share deals resulted in a
subsidiary being bought out.
