clearly defeated by a show of hands; a lengthy ballot had to be then held
and the motion passed.
Costs of the share deal controversy are expected to exceed IPounds 5m, and
reduce pre-tax profits in 1991 by 17 per cent.
A High Court investigation into the affair is imminent.
